        <num>CC 747</num>
        <heading>747.  Division of dominant estate</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 747.  Division of dominant estate.
If the dominant estate is divided, the servitude remains due to each part, provided that no additional burden is imposed on the servient estate.  Thus, in case of a right of passage, all the owners are bound to exercise that right through the same place.</p>
        </content>
